== About ==
In its current form, supports reading, erasing and writing program and config memory 
for the following devices:
- PIC18F452
- PIC18F4520

See the following page to download the ICSP kernel driver and a bit of documentation:
http://www.pavius.net/2011/06/lpicp-the-embedded-linux-pic-programmer/

== Compiling ==
The build environment supports both running on x86 (without the ICSP driver) and ppc. 

To compile for ppc:
- cd to build/ppc/debug
- cmake ../.. -DCMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE=../tc-eldk-ppc-8xx.cmake -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug
- make

== Not implemented yet ==
- Read/Program EEPROM
- Program at offset/selective program
- Read to HEX record

